CENTRAL STATES LIFE INSURANCE COMPANY, a Missouri Corporation, Appellant, v. James William CHILTON, Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 6, 1935. For opinion below, see 8 F. Supp. 778, affirmed on rehearing 8 F. Supp. 961. John F. Pierce, of Denver, Colo. (Wm. E. Hutton, of Denver, Colo., on the brief), for appellant. Henry E. Lutz, of Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, McDERMOTT, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed, with instructions to vacate the injunctive order of January 15, 1935, on authority of Louisville Joint Stock Land Bank v. Radford, 55 S. Ct. 854, 79 L. Ed. -, holding subsection (s), § 75, of the Bankruptcy Act (11 USCA § 203 (s), unconstitutional.
